Majuscule script (Coptic Majuscule), primarily from a single scribe with contributions by different hands in the scholia. Written in Uncial letters. Contains marginal notes and symbols indicating lectionary divisions, cross-references, and patristic scholia. 6th to 7th century Egypt The codex likely did not come to Europe before the 9th century. It arrived in Lower Italy before the 12th century, then moved to the Abbey of S. Denis in Paris, France. It was owned by René Marchal in the second half of the 16th century and Cardinal F. Rochefoucaud in 1636, who donated it to the Jesuit College of Clermont in Paris. The manuscript came to the Vatican in 1785. Owners: René Marchal, Cardinal F. Rochefoucaud.
